The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 09 September is 306,555 (544.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 September, there were 13,205 new confirmed cases (23.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 August, there were 7,687 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 72% (5518 extra cases).
